  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). One factor — discretization error — carries an achieved level below the required level; the overall assessment is nonetheless recorded as Accepted under Medium assurance, creating an inconsistency that should trigger COMPOUND-03.",
